# Work on PRD

Work through a PRD's issues in dependency order. Default execution model: one integration feature branch, with parallel git worktrees for independent AFK issues, merged back and cleaned up at the end.

## Input

The user provides a project slug or path (e.g., `auth` or `{{.plans_dir}}auth/`).

If none provided, ask: "Which PRD should I work on? (project slug or path)"

## Workflow states

```
{{join " → " .workflow_states}}
```

## Process

### 1. Read the PRD and issues

Read `{{.plans_dir}}{slug}/prd.yaml` and all files in `{{.plans_dir}}{slug}/issues/`.

If no issue files exist, tell the user: "This PRD has no implementation issues. Run `/bender-prd-to-issues` first."

### 2. Run dispatch

Run `{{.commands.dispatch}} {slug}` and wait for it to exit. Dispatch handles the full implementation loop: integration branch setup, parallel worktrees per AFK issue, sub-agent spawning, prefixed log streaming, merge-back in dependency order, and worktree cleanup. The skill body's job is just to invoke it.

Exit codes:

- **0** — every issue is `done`. Proceed to §6.
- **2** — only HITL issues remain. The HITL summary is on stdout — surface it to the user and stop.
- **non-zero (other)** — dispatch is stuck (typically blocked issues with no AFK candidates ready). Inspect the output, mark issues, and re-run.

Sub-agent stdout is streamed as `[issue-N] ...` so you can watch progress. Full per-issue logs land at `.plan-bender/logs/{slug}/{id}.log`.

### 6. Open the combined PR

```bash
git push -u origin <user>/<slug>
```

Open one PR off `<user>/<slug>` to the default branch. Title: the PRD title. Body:

- one bullet per issue (id, title, key acceptance)
- aggregated test plan from each issue's verification

### 7. Status report

Use `{{.commands.context}} {slug}` to get current issue counts per track.

```text
PRD: <project name>
Done:        <count>
In Review:   <count>
Blocked:     <count> (<issue IDs>)
QA:          <count>
Remaining:   <count> (<issue list>)
Points done: <sum> / <total>
PR:          <integration PR URL>

Track coverage:
{{range .tracks}}
  {{.}}:     <done>/<total>
{{end}}
```

Update `prd.yaml` status to `complete` when all issues are done.
{{if .has_backend_sync}}

## Linear sync

When `prd.yaml` has `linear.project_id`, the plan has been synced to Linear. In this case:

- **Issue updates** flow through `bender-implement-issue`, which handles per-issue Linear sync automatically
- **PRD completion**: when setting `prd.yaml` status to `complete`, also update the Linear project:

```bash
linear api --method POST --body '{"query":"mutation{projectUpdate(id:\"{linear.project_id}\",input:{state:\"completed\"}){success}}"}'
```

Linear updates are best-effort — if they fail, log the failure and continue.
{{end}}
